      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "handler",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The block to execute when the transition changes from interactive to noninteractive. The block has no return value and takes the following parameter:"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Your handler block is executed any time the transition changes from interactive to noninteractive, including when the transition ends or is cancelled. When the user cancels a transition, UIKit executes your context block, calls the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontroller/1621485-viewwilldisappear"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method on the presented view controller, and finally calls the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontroller/1621510-viewwillappear"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method on the original view controller to signal that it is once again visible.  "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrollertransitioncoordinatorcontext/2097567-interactive"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of the context object to determine the current interactivity of the transition. You can also use the value of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrollertransitioncoordinatorcontext/2097568-cancelled"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to determine an appropriate course of action. For example, if the transition was cancelled, you might remove any extra views that were added to the view hierarchy by a previous call to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrollertransitioncoordinator/1619300-animatealongsidetransition"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrollertransitioncoordinator/1619295-animatealongsidetransitioninview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can call this method multiple times to register multiple blocks. All of the registered blocks are executed when the transition state changes. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
